meta {
  name: Get My Permissions
  type: http
  seq: 17
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/users/manage/me/permissions?branchId=37e8cb33-9c10-4778-bc4c-20490e1c0f75
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

params:query {
  branchId: 37e8cb33-9c10-4778-bc4c-20490e1c0f75
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

docs {
  The **current user's** permissions **at a specific branch**, across the **full
  system catalogue**. The caller (person + tenant) comes from the bearer token;
  the branch is the **required `branchId` query param**.

  - `branchId` (**required**) ‚Äî the branch to resolve for. Must belong to the
    caller's tenant (validated server-side; a foreign/unknown branch ‚Üí not-found,
    so a client can't read another tenant's branch). Omitting it ‚Üí `400`.

  The role used is the one the user holds **at that branch** (a branch-level
  `UserBranchProfile`, else a tenant-level one ‚Äî e.g. `business_admin` /
  `administrator` ‚Äî which applies at every branch). So the **same user can get
  different permissions for different branches**: pass a different `branchId` to
  see that branch's result.

  Returns the user's **granted** permissions at this branch ‚Äî
  `{ role, branchModules, modules, allowed }`:

  - `role`: `{ key, label }` ‚Äî the role driving the permissions at this branch
    (the resolved baseline role). `null` when the user has no assignment here.
  - `branchModules`: `[{ moduleKey, label }]` ‚Äî the modules **enabled for this
    branch** (in canonical module order), regardless of the user's role.
  - `modules`: array of `{ moduleKey, moduleLabel, moduleAllowed, permissions }`,
    where `permissions` is a flat array of the **allowed `permissionKey`s** in that
    module (e.g. `["admin:view", "admin:edit"]`). Only modules with at least one
    allowed permission are included, so every emitted group has
    `moduleAllowed: true`. Catalogue order is preserved.
  - `allowed`: flat array of every `permissionKey` where `allowed === true` (e.g.
    `["admin:view", "admin:edit", "admin:manage_users"]`) ‚Äî the union of all the
    module `permissions` arrays; the frontend keys off this for show/hide.

  Effective value: `allowed = (module enabled for the branch) AND (branch override
  ?? role baseline)`. The module gate is the branch's enabled modules
  (`branch_modules`), and "special" permissions are the per-user overrides for
  **this branch only** (`user_branch_permissions` where `branchId` = the queried
  branch) ‚Äî grants/denies at other branches never leak in. Set those overrides via
  Update Branch Permissions.

  A permission granted by the role but whose module is not enabled at the branch is
  therefore omitted (disabled at this branch). If the user has **no assignment** at
  the branch, `modules` is empty and `allowed` is `[]`.
}
